{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Ruckus Wireless |model=ZoneFlex 7055 |upc=506016730042 |asin=B00E6I4TPE |fcc_date=02/20/2013 |manuf_country=China |is_manuf=No |type=access point |fcc_id=S9GZF7055 |ic_id=5912A-ZF7055 |pwr_v=48 |pwr_amp=0.62 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Atheros |cpu1_model=AR9344 |fla1_brand=Spansion |ram1=128 |ram1_brand=Nanya |ram1_model=NT5TU32M16DG-AC |ram1_num=2 |wi1_chip1_brand=Atheros |wi1_chip1_model=AR9344 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |wi2_chip1_brand=Atheros |wi2_chip1_model=AR9582 |wi2_802dot11_protocols=an |wi2_ant_conn=U.FL |wi2_txchains=2 |wi2_rxchains=2 |wi2_sstreams=2 |eth_cpu=true |eth_chip2_brand=Atheros |sw_brand=Atheros |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |802dot11_protocols=abgn |default_ip=192.168.0.1 or If you have dhcp server the ap is getting ip addres from dhcp server. |default_user=admin or super |default_pass=sp-admin |oui=8C:0C:90 |oui_eth=8C:0C:90 }} ''ZoneFlex 7055 Access Point''
Per the FCC photos... *The 2.4GHz radio (AR9344) is using 2x [http://www.skyworksinc.com/Product.aspx?ProductID=966 '''Skyworks''' ( / '''SiGe''') SE2611T (2611T) 2.4GHz WLAN Front End IC]s. *The 5GHz radio (AR9582) is using 2x [http://www.skyworksinc.com/uploads/documents/SE5007T_DS.pdf '''Skyworks''' ( / '''SiGe''') SE5007T (5007T) 5GHz WLAN Front End IC]s. *RAM appears to be 2x '''Nanya''' NT5TU32M16DG-AC (64MB each, 128MB total) *"Wall-E2_PD_Board V2.1" is silkscreened on the PoE board.
Manuf. by USI Shenzhen? (USI-SZ on the FCC sample label)
Default settings are per the FCC ''manual''.
Presumed 8C:0C:90 OUI based on the label affixed to the FCC EUT (external photos)...
